job_info.title: Network Security Engineer: 1. Skills / Strengths / Key Skills • Expertise in ﬁrewall conﬁguration and management (Fortinet, Palo Alto, Cisco ASA, Check Point, Juniper). • Strong hands-on experience with network protocols (TCP/IP, BGP, OSPF, IPSec, GRE, SSL). • Advanced knowledge of intrusion detection/prevention systems (IDS/IPS), VPNs, and web application ﬁrewalls (WAF). • Experience with network access control systems (Cisco ISE, Aruba ClearPass). • Familiarity with SIEM tools (Splunk, QRadar, LogRhythm) for log analysis and incident investigation. • Strong troubleshooting skills in complex network and security environments. • Ability to implement and manage security policies, ACLs, NAT rules across different vendor platforms. • Experience with automation and scripting (Python, Bash, Ansible) is a plus. • Familiarity with cloud security practices in AWS, Azure, or GCP. • Strong documentation and communication skills. 2. Experience / Responsibilities / Requirements • Minimum 5 years of hands-on experience in Network Security Engineering roles. • Responsible for designing, implementing, and managing secure network infrastructure across multi-vendor environments. • Perform regular vulnerability assessments and penetration testing in coordination with the cybersecurity team. • Monitor and respond to security incidents and network anomalies. • Collaborate with internal teams and vendors to support business continuity and disaster recovery planning. • Develop and maintain security baselines, conﬁgurations, and hardening standards for routers, switches, and ﬁrewalls. • Conduct periodic audits to ensure compliance with industry standards (ISO 27001, NIST, etc.). • Manage network segmentation projects to reduce attack surfaces and enhance internal security posture. • Lead network security upgrades and technology refresh initiatives. • Support internal/external audits and provide technical documentation as needed. 3. Qualiﬁcation / Education • Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related ﬁeld. • Industry certiﬁcations preferred: o Mandatory: CCNP Security / Fortinet NSE 4 or higher o Preferred: Palo Alto PCNSE, CEH, CISSP, or CompTIA Security+ • Continuous learning mindset with proven history of keeping up to date with new threats, trends, and technologies in the network security domain.
